cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a new framework for fluid segmentation and detection in retinal OCT images using a fully convolutional neural network. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of machine learning algorithms such as random forest classification and leave-one-out cross-validation suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the use of medical imaging techniques and the focus on retinal diseases suggest that it may belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of neural networks suggests that it may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
